          Yes, non-Indigenous people are welcome. There are competitive and traditional pow-wows.
          In the competitive pow-wows, the dancers and the drummers have numbers, and in the traditional pow-wows, they don’t.
          That’s the main difference. Competitive, some people win, traditional ones there are no winners, everyone wins. In the pow-wows, there is crafting, food, traditional songs and dances. There is also contemporary dance. Fancy shawl counts among the contemporary dances, but contemporary doesn’t mean new from this year. It means new from 1920.»</p>
